        <h2>Orientation Detection</h2>
        <p>
            This straightforward example shows how two strings of text determine whether or not an element is visible in different orientations.
            This will change on mobile devices when you rotate the device.
            On desktop, the orientation is almost always reported as landscape.
        </p>
        <HighlightCode Language="html" Full="true" HeaderIcon="mdi-language-html5" HeaderBGcolor="#f06529" HeaderTitle="HTML"
                     Content="PHAgY2xhc3M9InNob3ctZm9yLWxhbmRzY2FwZSI+WW91IGFyZSBpbiBsYW5kc2NhcGUgb3JpZW50YXRpb24uPC9wPgo8cCBjbGFzcz0ic2hvdy1mb3ItcG9ydHJhaXQiPllvdSBhcmUgaW4gcG9ydHJhaXQgb3JpZW50YXRpb24uPC9wPg==" />
        <p class="show-for-landscape">You are in landscape orientation.</p>
        <p class="show-for-portrait">You are in portrait orientation.</p>
        <hr />
    </SectionLeft>
</SectionWrapper>

